Class AdminPageActivity

    • android.content.Context

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback

    public class AdminPageActivity
extends ActionBarActivity
    Activity is responsible for presenting all the menus accessible for the admin On pressing any of the menu, the admin is redirected to the corresponding activity associated with that menu On first login, the admin has an added task to enter the tablet id which would be stored in DatabaseHelper.configParametersTable table. This class handles animation of the menus to be visible on the activity in a precalculated delay

        private boolean isSetupComplete()

        Returns:

        Function to verify whether the tablet name has been entered by the admin for the first login If the tablet name is initialized and its present in its internal local database, the return value makes sure that the dialog box to enter the tabletName is not visible for successive logins and the admin is only presented directly with all the menus of the admin dashboard.
